<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Iran, Mazandaran Province, Panjab village, unnamed brook (left tributary of Haraz River); 
<geoCoordinate degrees="36" direction="north" minutes="05" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="52.818" value="36.098003">36°05'52.818&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
/
<geoCoordinate degrees="52" direction="east" minutes="15" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="15.987" value="52.25444">52°15'15.987&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
(locality no. 152); 955 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Northern Iran. Species endemic to the Alborz Mountains (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figure 39. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471961" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae inhabit small rivers at middle and high altitude in the central Alborz. Altitudinal range of sampling sites 750-2438 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figure 39. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471961" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">39</figureCitation>
). Most frequently found at altitudes above 1000 m a.s.l. At high altitudes often syntopic with 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. (C.) iranicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="iranicus" subGenus="C.">E. (C.) iranicus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="main morphological diagnostics of larvae">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Main morphological diagnostics of larvae.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(i) abdominal terga as on Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="F40" captionText="Figure 40. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F, G middle leg in dorsal view H, I abdominal terga J, K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view) L-N abdominal sterna II-VI." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471962" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">40H, I</figureCitation>
; (ii) abdominal sterna II-VI with circular central medial macula of various intensity (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="F40" captionText="Figure 40. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F, G middle leg in dorsal view H, I abdominal terga J, K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view) L-N abdominal sterna II-VI." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471962" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">40B, L-N</figureCitation>
); (iii) tergum X with postero-lateral projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I, J gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape K abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection) L sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471964" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41K</figureCitation>
, arrow), (iv) femora without medial hypodermal spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="F40" captionText="Figure 40. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F, G middle leg in dorsal view H, I abdominal terga J, K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view) L-N abdominal sterna II-VI." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471962" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">40F, G</figureCitation>
); (v) gill plates VII (in natural position from ventral view) wide (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="F40" captionText="Figure 40. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F, G middle leg in dorsal view H, I abdominal terga J, K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view) L-N abdominal sterna II-VI." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471962" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">40J, K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I, J gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape K abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection) L sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471964" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41H-J</figureCitation>
); (vi) setae on abdominal terga hair-like (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I, J gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape K abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection) L sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471964" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41E</figureCitation>
); (vii) gill plates III with well-developed projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Epeorus (Caucasiron) alborzicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I, J gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape K abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection) L sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471964" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomy</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species was described based on larvae collected from Alborz Mts. (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" author="Hrivniak, Ľ" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="71 - 102" refId="B21" refString="Hrivniak, Ľ, Sroka, P, Bojkova, J, Godunko, RJ, Imanpour Namin, J, Bagheri, S, Nejat, F, Abdoli, A, Staniczek, AH, 2020a. Diversity and distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in Iran, with descriptions of three new species. ZooKeys 947: 71 - 102, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" title="Diversity and distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in Iran, with descriptions of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" volume="947" year="2020 a">Hrivniak et al. 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). Imagines not described.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The type series is currently deposited in SMNS, IECA, and Natural History Museum and Genetic Resources, Department of Environment, Tehran, Iran (MMTT_DOE).</paragraph>
